    "type": "header",
    "text": "Diarrhoea",
    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "type": "callout",
    "text": "Definition: Passage of 3 or more loose or liquid stools per day. \n• Acute: < 2 weeks (Usually infectious).\n• Chronic: > 4 weeks."
  },
  {
    "type": "tab_group",
    "tabs": [
      {
        "title": "Mechanisms & Causes",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "header",
            "text": "Pathophysiological Mechanisms",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "items": [
              { "text": "Osmotic: Solutes in lumen retain water (e.g. Lactose Intolerance, Magnesium laxatives). Stops with fasting." },
              { "text": "Secretory: Active secretion of water/electrolytes (e.g. Cholera, Carcinoid). Persists with fasting." },
              { "text": "Inflammatory (Exudative): Damage to mucosa (e.g. Dysentery, IBD). Blood/pus present." },
              { "text": "Motility: Rapid transit (e.g. Thyrotoxicosis, IBS)." }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "header",
            "text": "Flash Card 34: Causes of Diarrhoea",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "accordion",
            "items": [
              {
                "title": "Acute Diarrhoea",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "list", "items": [
                    { "text": "Viral: Rotavirus, Norovirus." },
                    { "text": "Bacterial: Salmonella, Shigella, Campylobacter, E. coli, Cholera (Vibrio)." },
                    { "text": "Parasitic: Giardia, Amoebiasis." },
                    { "text": "Toxins: Staph aureus (Food poisoning)." },
                    { "text": "Drugs: Antibiotics (C. diff), Laxatives." }
                  ]}
                ]
              },
              {
                "title": "Chronic Diarrhoea",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "list", "items": [
                    { "text": "Colonic: IBD (Ulcerative Colitis, Crohn's), Colorectal CA, Irritable Bowel Syndrome (IBS)." },
                    { "text": "Small Bowel: Malabsorption (Coeliac, Tropical Sprue), Giardiasis." },
                    { "text": "Pancreatic: Chronic Pancreatitis (Steatorrhoea), Cystic Fibrosis." },
                    { "text": "Endocrine: Thyrotoxicosis, Diabetes (Autonomic), Carcinoid Syndrome, Zollinger-Ellison." },
                    { "text": "Drugs: Metformin, PPIs, NSAIDs." }
                  ]}
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
